You are working on a single-user Dungeons & Dragons 5e spellbook application.

## Core Objective
Build a fast, immersive spellbook-style web app for managing spells and spell slots during gameplay. The app must prioritize usability during live play over architectural complexity.

## Hard Constraints (DO NOT VIOLATE)
- This is a frontend-only application in MVP.
- No backend, no APIs, no servers.
- No authentication or user accounts.
- No cloud sync or cross-device state sharing.
- No database layer (beyond browser localStorage).
- No rules engine or automated game logic.
- No expansion into full D&D Beyond-like system.

## Scope Discipline
- If a feature is not explicitly required in MVP.md, do NOT implement it.
- Prefer removing complexity over adding abstraction.
- Do not introduce new libraries unless necessary and justified.
- Do not refactor unrelated code when making a local change.

## State & Persistence Rules
- All persistence must use browser localStorage.
- State should be simple, explicit, and inspectable.
- Do not introduce external state management libraries unless asked.

## Code Style
- Prefer simple, readable React patterns.
- Use functional components and hooks.
- Avoid over-engineering abstractions early.
- Keep component hierarchy shallow where possible.

## UI Philosophy
- The app should feel like a magical spellbook, not a dashboard.
- Functionality during gameplay is more important than visual polish.
- UI complexity must serve usability, not aesthetics alone.

## Decision Behavior
- When uncertain, choose the simplest working solution.
- If a change risks expanding scope, stop and ask for clarification.
- Do not “future-proof” beyond MVP requirements.

## File Discipline
- Respect PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md.
- Place code in the correct feature folder.
- Do not reorganize folder structure without explicit instruction.

## Refactoring Rule
Do not refactor existing working code unless it is required to complete the current task or fix a bug.

## Feature Expansion Rule
If a request implies expanding beyond MVP scope, explicitly identify it as out of scope and do not implement it.

## Architecture Rule
Do not introduce new architectural layers (services, repositories, abstractions) unless explicitly requested.